article.headline: S. Utah 69, UMKC 56
article.story: CEDAR CITY, Utah -- Matt Massey scored 14 points, Matt Hodgson had 10 points and 10 rebounds, and Southern Utah broke away in the closing minutes for a 69-56 victory over UMKC Saturday night. The score was tied at 50 with six minutes to play, then Massey scored on a three-point play that ignited a 13-2 run by the Thunderbirds (6-15, 2-8 Summit). The final score was Southern Utah's largest lead of the game. Southern Utah outrebounded UMKC 42-25 and scored 38 points in the paint while holding UMKC to 10. Jay Couisnard had 18 points and Trey McKinney-Jones 14 for the Kangaroos (9-12, 3-7). Southern Utah made 49 percent of its field-goal tries -- 61 percent in the first half -- while UMKC made 34 percent for the game.
